{"id":14880781,"mediaExerciseId":"9bcbcca1-e6cb-4719-91c0-79794c805f0d","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"3","chapterTitle":"Working with Financial Statements","groupId":612272,"groupTitle":"Work The Web","isPremium":true,"sectionName":"3.5","sectionTitle":"Using Financial Statement Information","pageNumber":79,"solutions":[{"id":6366705,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will evaluate the ratios that are available on the textbook and on a business website. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"In the textbook, there are several ratios that are presented which can be used to evaluate the profitability of the firm. However, in the website only a few ratios are shown. \n\nThe ratios presented in the website are: **Current Ratio, Quick Ratio, Total Debt Ratio, Long-Term Debt Ratio, and Payout Ratio**. The reason why only these ratios are shown is because information from these ratios are already enough in order to determine the overall trend of the company whether they are profitable or not. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Aside from this, there are several factors that cannot be quantified which can also affect the profitability of the company so using only the ratios given in the website is already enough to determine the future of the firm/company.\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"b67798cb-726b-44b2-b00c-2de47662232b","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbna